  <heading>BRKA</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Break after first true condition</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction sets the destination predicate elements up to and including
the first active and true source element to true, then sets
subsequent elements to false.</para>
      <para>Inactive elements in the destination predicate register remain unmodified or
are set to zero, depending on whether merging or zeroing
predication is selected.
This instruction does not set the condition flags.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
  </desc>
